I was very nervous going in.

00:39:12.470 --> 00:39:13.680 align:middle line:90%
You knew that, you know?

00:39:13.680 --> 00:39:15.210 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know what to expect.

00:39:15.210 --> 00:39:17.430 align:middle line:84%
And it does kind
of calm you, and I

00:39:17.430 --> 00:39:20.130 align:middle line:84%
can't get over that I was
in there for that long.

00:39:20.130 --> 00:39:22.470 align:middle line:90%
I really can't get past that.

00:39:22.470 --> 00:39:24.660 align:middle line:84%
It just seemed like
five minutes and like

00:39:24.660 --> 00:39:28.330 align:middle line:84%
I had this whole long time
to wait, and it was over,

00:39:28.330 --> 00:39:29.130 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:39:29.130 --> 00:39:31.690 align:middle line:90%


00:39:31.690 --> 00:39:34.530 align:middle line:84%
>> I wrote reunions because I
wanted to get this information

00:39:34.530 --> 00:39:35.370 align:middle line:90%
out.

00:39:35.370 --> 00:39:38.850 align:middle line:84%
I think that whatever one
makes of these findings

00:39:38.850 --> 00:39:43.710 align:middle line:84%
about the apparitions
seen in a psychomanteum

00:39:43.710 --> 00:39:45.000 align:middle line:90%
is important work.

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:52.860 align:middle line:84%
And for me, of course, the main
response I want to see happen

00:39:52.860 --> 00:39:56.820 align:middle line:84%
is my colleagues in
psychology and so on--

00:39:56.820 --> 00:39:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I want to see them
reproducing this phenomenon

00:39:59.430 --> 00:40:01.170 align:middle line:90%
and seeing what they make of it.

00:40:01.170 --> 00:40:03.060 align:middle line:90%
And that's already happened.

00:40:03.060 --> 00:40:06.150 align:middle line:84%
To my knowledge, so far
nine other psychologists

00:40:06.150 --> 00:40:09.670 align:middle line:90%
have fully replicated this.

00:40:09.670 --> 00:40:12.910 align:middle line:84%
One of these
individuals is a woman

00:40:12.910 --> 00:40:17.830 align:middle line:84%
who works in Houston at a
very well known hospice there.

00:40:17.830 --> 00:40:21.730 align:middle line:84%
She's been a hospice counselor
dealing with the terminally ill

00:40:21.730 --> 00:40:24.730 align:middle line:84%
and their families now for
a long, long time-- very

00:40:24.730 --> 00:40:27.130 align:middle line:90%
well-respected in the community.

00:40:27.130 --> 00:40:29.320 align:middle line:84%
And she's using
this for therapy,

00:40:29.320 --> 00:40:32.230 align:middle line:84%
to help people, you
know, face death

00:40:32.230 --> 00:40:35.110 align:middle line:84%
and to face the
losses that they've

00:40:35.110 --> 00:40:38.790 align:middle line:90%
gone through in their lives.

00:40:38.790 --> 00:40:42.790 align:middle line:84%
>> In helping people walk
through the grief process

00:40:42.790 --> 00:40:45.140 align:middle line:84%
and knowing that there
is life after death--

00:40:45.140 --> 00:40:47.230 align:middle line:84%
it's tremendously
healing for them.

00:40:47.230 --> 00:40:49.420 align:middle line:10%
Actually, in my work,
I've never worked

00:40:49.420 --> 00:40:51.370 align:middle line:10%
with a dying patient
who did not have

00:40:51.370 --> 00:40:52.720 align:middle line:10%
an apparitional experience.

00:40:52.720 --> 00:40:53.770 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's 100%.

00:40:53.770 --> 00:40:55.390 align:middle line:90%
You can write this in stone.

00:40:55.390 --> 00:40:58.540 align:middle line:84%
If a person is terminally
ill, when it's close to death,

00:40:58.540 --> 00:41:03.460 align:middle line:84%
they're going to have an
apparitional experience.

00:41:03.460 --> 00:41:06.150 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one thing
that we do in hospice--

00:41:06.150 --> 00:41:08.290 align:middle line:84%
if a person has had an
apparitional experience

00:41:08.290 --> 00:41:10.750 align:middle line:84%
or if they've had a
reunion, that person becomes

00:41:10.750 --> 00:41:12.600 align:middle line:84%
top priority,
because we know death

00:41:12.600 --> 00:41:16.150 align:middle line:84%
is imminent, that it's always
within one week or two weeks

00:41:16.150 --> 00:41:17.400 align:middle line:90%
that a person is going to die.

00:41:17.400 --> 00:41:19.920 align:middle line:84%
No matter-- if we think
maybe they've got six months,

00:41:19.920 --> 00:41:22.920 align:middle line:84%
we're not real sure if hospice
even ought to take them in,

00:41:22.920 --> 00:41:25.200 align:middle line:84%
but once a person has that
apparitional experience,

00:41:25.200 --> 00:41:27.210 align:middle line:84%
if they have a
terminal illness, we

00:41:27.210 --> 00:41:30.400 align:middle line:84%
know that person is greeting
them, they're loving them,

00:41:30.400 --> 00:41:33.896 align:middle line:84%
and they're escorting
them to the other side.

00:41:33.896 --> 00:41:35.520 align:middle line:84%
And then people in
bereavement groups--

00:41:35.520 --> 00:41:38.580 align:middle line:84%
there's a high number
who also have a reunion.

00:41:38.580 --> 00:41:40.530 align:middle line:84%
So when-- I was very
familiar with this.

00:41:40.530 --> 00:41:42.780 align:middle line:84%
It was like a common
everyday occurrence,

00:41:42.780 --> 00:41:44.770 align:middle line:84%
and hearing Dr. Moody
speak for the first time,

00:41:44.770 --> 00:41:47.070 align:middle line:90%
I was on the edge of my seat.

00:41:47.070 --> 00:41:50.220 align:middle line:84%
I said, how could he do this
under controlled circumstances?

00:41:50.220 --> 00:41:52.214 align:middle line:84%
It was just incredible
to me, the thought

00:41:52.214 --> 00:41:53.130 align:middle line:90%
that he could do that.

00:41:53.130 --> 00:41:56.450 align:middle line:90%


00:41:56.450 --> 00:42:00.110 align:middle line:84%
62 people have been through
the oracle in Houston.

00:42:00.110 --> 00:42:04.710 align:middle line:84%
Out of the 62, 48 have had some
type of reunion experience.

00:42:04.710 --> 00:42:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And actually I call mine oracle,
because oracle means a place

00:42:08.790 --> 00:42:10.780 align:middle line:90%
for acquiring wisdom.

00:42:10.780 --> 00:42:15.030 align:middle line:84%
And I have found that, even
when a person comes and has

00:42:15.030 --> 00:42:19.620 align:middle line:84%
a session, even if they do
not have a reunion, something

00:42:19.620 --> 00:42:21.620 align:middle line:90%
very profound--

00:42:21.620 --> 00:42:24.540 align:middle line:84%
a deep psychological--
and deep psychic change

00:42:24.540 --> 00:42:27.042 align:middle line:90%
takes place for them.

00:42:27.042 --> 00:42:31.330 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, it's such an
intriguing idea that,

00:42:31.330 --> 00:42:37.230 align:middle line:84%
in the ancient world, there was
an institution for 1,000 years

00:42:37.230 --> 00:42:40.860 align:middle line:84%
where you could go, and there
you could have the experience

00:42:40.860 --> 00:42:45.150 align:middle line:84%
of seeing, and visiting with,
and talking with departed

00:42:45.150 --> 00:42:47.600 align:middle line:90%
relatives.

00:42:47.600 --> 00:42:53.030 align:middle line:84%
And I wouldn't be too surprised
if, over the next few years,

00:42:53.030 --> 00:42:59.750 align:middle line:84%
this institution reappears
in our modern world.

00:42:59.750 --> 00:43:05.285 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so looking forward to
seeing that as it develops,

00:43:05.285 --> 00:43:08.015 align:middle line:84%
to see how people respond
to this, to see how

00:43:08.015 --> 00:43:11.360 align:middle line:90%
our society integrates this.

00:43:11.360 --> 00:43:13.940 align:middle line:84%
My hope for it is
that it will turn out

00:43:13.940 --> 00:43:16.460 align:middle line:84%
to be something
very therapeutic,

00:43:16.460 --> 00:43:19.190 align:middle line:84%
and that it will help
people who are undergoing

00:43:19.190 --> 00:43:23.060 align:middle line:84%
prolonged grief, who just
can't let go of a loved

00:43:23.060 --> 00:43:27.423 align:middle line:84%
one lost to death, and for
that reason are miserable

00:43:27.423 --> 00:43:30.141 align:middle line:90%
themselves.

00:43:30.141 --> 00:43:31.800 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
most common things

00:43:31.800 --> 00:43:34.080 align:middle line:84%
that we hear people
say at that time

00:43:34.080 --> 00:43:38.680 align:middle line:84%
is, if I only had
five more minutes.

00:43:38.680 --> 00:43:42.180 align:middle line:84%
What we can do now,
without a doubt,

00:43:42.180 --> 00:43:47.960 align:middle line:84%
is that we can give people
that five more minutes.

00:43:47.960 --> 00:43:54.620 align:middle line:84%
If we can help people like
this turn themselves around

00:43:54.620 --> 00:44:00.640 align:middle line:84%
and open up to hope and to a new
life, then I think all of this

00:44:00.640 --> 00:44:03.047 align:middle line:90%
will be justified.

00:44:03.047 --> 00:45:03.446 align:middle line:90%